<TITLE> Roadside bomb kills four police in Afghan southeast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KHOST, Afghanistan, Oct 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Four Afghan policemen were killed in southeastern Afghanistan on Thursday when a roadside bomb hit their vehicle, a provincial police officer said. Three other policemen were wounded in the attack, in a remote border area of Khost province, Colonel Wazir Badshah told reporters. A Taliban spokesman, speaking by telephone from an undisclosed location, said the blast was the work of the Islamic militant group that is fighting against the Afghan government and the Western troops stationed in the country. The past two years have seen Afghanistan's worst spell of bloodshed since the Taliban's ouster in 2001, with thousands of people kill
